  To set environment variables in Ray init, you can use the `runtime_env` parameter and pass a dictionary with the environment variables you want to set. For example:
```
ray.init(
    runtime_env={
        "env_vars": {
            "FOO": "bar"
        }
    }
)
```
This will set the environment variable `FOO` to `bar` in all Ray workers.

Alternatively, you can use the `env_vars` parameter in the `ray.init()` function to set environment variables. For example:
```
ray.init(
    env_vars={
        "FOO": "bar"
    }
)
```
This will also set the environment variable `FOO` to `bar` in all Ray workers.

Note that environment variables set in the `runtime_env` or `env_vars` parameters will override any existing environment variables with the same name on the cluster.
